Colombian Stock Movers: Grupo Aval, Ecopetrol Fall; EEB Rises

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-08-10T21:10:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/colombian-stock-movers-bancolombia-ecopetrol-pacific-rubiales.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 5 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.1 percent to 13,071.59, while the
Colcap Index added 0.3 percent to 1,582.20.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL)  SA,  Colombia ’s
biggest financial holding company, fell 1.6 percent to 1,200
pesos amid renewed concern the European sovereign debt crisis is
worsening and that the global economic recovery is faltering.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , the nation’s state-controlled
oil company, slid 0.8 percent to 3,670 pesos.  Empresa de Energia de Bogota SA (EEB)  , Colombia’s
second-biggest electricity distributor, jumped 10.7 percent to
1,435 pesos. EEB, as the company is known, said in a statement
yesterday that its shareholders approved plans to sell as much
as 1 trillion pesos ($556.8 million) of shares. The stock
rebounded from its 2.2 percent decline yesterday “after the
market absorbed the share sale news and awaits details on the
amount and price,” said Alejandra Alvarez, an equity analyst at
Cia. Profesionales de Bolsa SA brokerage in Bogota.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
